<subSubSection id="C304652A4D243249FF774445FA4232DA" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" type="key">
<keyStep id="30EA2E044D243249FF774445FA42337A" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF774445FA423345" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF774445FA423345" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">1. Elytra yellow, humeral region yellow. Pronotum dark brown with lateral sides yellow. Phallus broad medially, as wide as phallobase in ventral view.............................................................................. 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF77441FFA42337A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF77441FFA42337A" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">1’. Elytra dark brown, humeral region yellow. Pronotum dark brown with lateral sides yellow. Phallus broad medially, but narrower than phallobase in ventral view.......................................................................... 3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30EA2E044D243249FF7744D0FA4233F5" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF7744D0FA4233B0" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF7744D0FA4233B0" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
2. Maxillary palpomere 2 twice longer than 3. Phallus constricted at distal 3/4. Parameres double-hooked apically......................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB7844F7FA4233B0" bold="true" box="[1176,1436,1698,1720]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB7844F7FAF633BF" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Gorham" baseAuthorityYear="1884" box="[1176,1320,1698,1720]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Cladocalon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiriquense" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB7844F7FAF633BF" bold="true" box="[1176,1320,1698,1720]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">C. chiriquense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957C84D243249FACE44F7FA4233B0" box="[1326,1436,1698,1719]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF774495FA4233F5" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF774495FA4233F5" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
2’. Maxillary palpomere 2 2.4× longer than palpomere 3. Phallus constricted at distal 2/3. Parameres with single apical hook..................................................................................... 
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB244488FA4233F5" bold="true" box="[1220,1436,1756,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB244488FA9733F5" authority="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova, 2022" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" box="[1220,1353,1756,1778]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Cladocalon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bugabense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB244488FA9733F5" bold="true" box="[1220,1353,1756,1778]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">C. bugabense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957C84D243249FAB04488FA4233F5" box="[1360,1436,1757,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30EA2E044D243249FF7744AFFA423260" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF7744AFFA42322A" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF7744AFFA42322A" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
3. Terminal palpomere of maxillary palpi constricted distally. Elytra dark brown with yellow stripes restricted to humeral region, and femur dark brown. Male genitalia with parameres presenting single apical hook.......... 
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB6D4542FA42322A" bold="true" box="[1165,1436,1815,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB6D4542FAF6322A" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1165,1320,1815,1837]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Calocladon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrionicum" status="comb. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB6D4542FAF6322A" bold="true" box="[1165,1320,1815,1837]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">C. histrionicum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957C84D243249FACE454DFA42322A" box="[1326,1436,1816,1837]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">comb. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF774560FA423260" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF774560FA423260" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">3’ Terminal palpomere of maxillary palpi rounded distally. Elytra dark brown with yellow stripes from humeral region to basal 1/3 or basal half......................................................................................... 4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30EA2E044D243249FF774525FA4232DA" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF774525FA4232A5" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF774525FA4232A5" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
4. Phallus medially broad, narrower than phallobase in ventral view, phallic folding weakly projected ventrally in lateral view. Parameral apex hooked.............................................................. 
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB2345D8FA4232A5" bold="true" box="[1219,1436,1933,1954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB2345D8FA9432A5" authority="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova, 2022" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" box="[1219,1354,1933,1954]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Cladocalon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB2345D8FA9432A5" bold="true" box="[1219,1354,1933,1954]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">C. mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957C84D243249FAB045D8FA4232A5" box="[1360,1436,1933,1954]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA136A14D243249FF7745FFFA4232DA" blockId="6.[151,1437,1552,2014]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<keyLead id="30EF95944D243249FF7745FFFA4232DA" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
4’. Phallus medially broad, almost as large as phallobase in ventral view, phallic folding strongly projected ventrally in lateral view. Parameral apex curved and pointed ventrally in lateral view............................... 
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB464592FA4232DA" bold="true" box="[1190,1436,1991,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">
<taxonomicName id="4C1E4D224D243249FB464592FA9432DA" authority="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova, 2022" authorityName="Nascimento &amp; Bocakova" authorityYear="2022" box="[1190,1354,1991,2013]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Cladocalon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guatemalense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B96AEAB34D243249FB464592FA9432DA" bold="true" box="[1190,1354,1991,2013]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="583">C. guatemalense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25957C84D243249FAB0459DFA4232DA" box="[1360,1436,1992,2013]" pageId="6" pageNumber="583" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
